<h2 id="who-its-for">🎯 Who Each Platform Is For</h2>

<strong>Choose Pabau if:</strong>
<ul>
<li>You're a med spa prioritizing clinical documentation and compliance</li>
<li>Your practice performs injectable treatments requiring detailed charting</li>
<li>You're scaling from 1-15 locations and want predictable costs</li>
<li>Medical director oversight requires comprehensive treatment records</li>
<li>You value implementation speed over maximum feature breadth</li>
</ul>

<strong>Choose Zenoti if:</strong>
<ul>
<li>You're operating 20+ locations with franchise-style management</li>
<li>Complex employee compensation requires integrated payroll</li>
<li>Retail revenue represents 25%+ of your business</li>
<li>You need advanced marketing automation and loyalty programs</li>
<li>Your organization has dedicated IT resources for implementation</li>
</ul>

For most med spa operators reading this comparison, Pabau represents the better fit. The clinical EMR depth, reasonable pricing, and implementation simplicity align with how aesthetic practices actually operate. Zenoti makes sense for a specific operator profile—large-scale, operationally complex, with resources to maximize their enterprise toolset.

